article.headline: Delaware State 61, Hampton 58
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Darrin Shine scored 13 points and hit three of Delaware State's seven 3-pointers Saturday night as the Hornets beat Hampton 61-58 and remained unbeaten in conference play. Delaware State (8-10, 6-0 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) held the Pirates to 16 first-half points in opening a 23-16 lead at the break, then held on. Hampton (5-9, 4-3) commited 19 turnovers that the Hornets turned into 17 points. The Pirates also missed 8 of 11 3-point shots and shot under 44 percent. Aaron Fleetwood added 12 points and Joe Dickens 11 for Delaware State. Jaz Cowan led the Pirates with 16 points and Rashad West had 14.
